WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:55.470
<b>My Turn</b>

3
00:02:10.360 --> 00:02:15.760
I've cried my heart out. 
I've whined enough, too.

4
00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:19.320
I've made my decision!

5
00:02:21.370 --> 00:02:24.890
I have to go. Everyone's fighting!

6
00:02:31.770 --> 00:02:38.260
I thought that they had a chance.
Was it just a dream?

7
00:02:38.980 --> 00:02:41.280
What did that damn shark do?

8
00:02:41.280 --> 00:02:42.720
I don't know.

9
00:02:42.720 --> 00:02:47.510
He just sprayed them with water, but they went flying, coughing up blood.

10
00:02:48.690 --> 00:02:51.550
I can kill humans like you

11
00:02:51.550 --> 00:02:57.060
without so much as touching you, if I have some water.

12
00:02:57.060 --> 00:02:59.300
That's the difference between 
fishmen and humans.

13
00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:00.610
Give me a break!

14
00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:09.660
This is no joke.

15
00:03:09.660 --> 00:03:15.260
Playing with a water gun for him is like getting hit with a shotgun for us.

16
00:03:15.260 --> 00:03:17.630
So this is the power of a shark?

17
00:03:17.630 --> 00:03:20.700
And he's in a class
by himself among fishmen.

18
00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:25.760
He's in another league.

19
00:03:25.760 --> 00:03:27.970
Die already.

20
00:03:27.970 --> 00:03:32.940
Your lives are not worth that much.

21
00:03:32.940 --> 00:03:33.940
Arlong!

22
00:03:34.730 --> 00:03:36.370
Big Sis Nami!

23
00:03:36.370 --> 00:03:37.440
Nami!

24
00:03:37.440 --> 00:03:39.210
Nacchan.

25
00:03:39.210 --> 00:03:45.410
Hey, Nami! I was just about to crush these two-bit pirates.

26
00:03:45.410 --> 00:03:47.700
Why'd you come here?

27
00:03:52.790 --> 00:03:55.460
To kill you.

28
00:03:57.690 --> 00:03:59.420
To kill...

29
00:04:00.030 --> 00:04:01.390
me?

30
00:04:05.700 --> 00:04:08.350
You never learn, do you?

31
00:04:08.350 --> 00:04:10.570
How many times did you try to kill me

32
00:04:10.570 --> 00:04:13.570
during the eight years you were with us?

33
00:04:14.350 --> 00:04:17.710
You tried assassination, 
poison, ambushes,

34
00:04:17.710 --> 00:04:20.070
but I'm still here.

35
00:04:21.140 --> 00:04:26.490
You should've learned that mere humans like you can never kill me.

36
00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:30.500
Now, listen. I won't kill you...

37
00:04:31.200 --> 00:04:34.700
and you can't escape from me.

38
00:04:35.870 --> 00:04:37.070
Nami,

39
00:04:37.650 --> 00:04:41.600
you'll be our surveyor forever.

40
00:04:42.970 --> 00:04:46.450
But, as you know, 
I'm a good-natured man.

41
00:04:46.450 --> 00:04:51.770
If possible, I want you to be our 
surveyor of your own free will.

42
00:04:55.600 --> 00:04:58.690
So, how about this?

43
00:04:58.690 --> 00:05:05.600
I intend to kill everyone here except you.

44
00:05:07.410 --> 00:05:11.800
If you're willing to come back to the Arlong Pirates

45
00:05:11.800 --> 00:05:14.870
and draw sea charts
as one of our officers,

46
00:05:15.700 --> 00:05:20.840
I don't mind letting those people from Cocoyashi Village live.

47
00:05:22.070 --> 00:05:26.610
These guys are finished, though.

48
00:05:26.610 --> 00:05:28.530
They went too far.

49
00:05:28.530 --> 00:05:31.010
The question is who you'll side with.

50
00:05:31.740 --> 00:05:35.980
You either join me now and 
be spared along with the villagers,

51
00:05:35.980 --> 00:05:40.990
or team up with these weaklings and try fighting me together.

52
00:05:40.990 --> 00:05:45.750
If you depend on these guys in the shape they're in,

53
00:05:45.750 --> 00:05:48.780
it'll clearly end in tragedy for you.

54
00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:53.370
Nami,

55
00:05:53.970 --> 00:05:56.460
are you a member of my crew?

56
00:05:56.460 --> 00:05:57.790
Or...

57
00:05:58.260 --> 00:06:00.250
their friend?

58
00:06:03.030 --> 00:06:04.960
How unfair!

59
00:06:04.960 --> 00:06:07.390
If I say I'm friends with 
Luffy and the others,

60
00:06:07.390 --> 00:06:09.180
everyone will get killed.

61
00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:11.420
And if I say I'm in Arlong's crew,

62
00:06:11.420 --> 00:06:13.890
then everyone from 
the village will be saved.

63
00:06:13.890 --> 00:06:16.930
It all depends on my decision!

64
00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:20.740
That's despicable!

65
00:06:20.740 --> 00:06:23.610
No matter what she chooses,
he's going to keep Nami in chains!

66
00:06:25.610 --> 00:06:27.070
Still!

67
00:06:31.450 --> 00:06:32.740
Luffy,

68
00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:39.370
help me!

69
00:06:40.210 --> 00:06:42.670
Of course I will!

70
00:06:45.990 --> 00:06:49.630
I must not doubt him!

71
00:06:53.510 --> 00:06:54.680
Everyone, I'm sorry!

72
00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:57.420
Please die with me!

73
00:06:59.980 --> 00:07:02.190
All right!

74
00:07:02.190 --> 00:07:03.920
We'll go for it!

75
00:07:04.790 --> 00:07:07.360
We'll fight!

76
00:07:08.350 --> 00:07:09.840
I see.

77
00:07:09.840 --> 00:07:13.370
Everyone wants to die.

78
00:07:20.080 --> 00:07:22.420
P-Please! Please!

79
00:07:23.130 --> 00:07:26.880
Live! Live! Live! Live! Live!

80
00:07:35.140 --> 00:07:36.180
Hm?

81
00:07:36.720 --> 00:07:38.090
What the?

82
00:07:41.100 --> 00:07:42.020
Finally!

83
00:07:42.510 --> 00:07:44.990
All that's left is to free his legs.

84
00:07:44.990 --> 00:07:46.340
Oh.

85
00:07:48.220 --> 00:07:49.860
So that's what you meant?

86
00:07:49.860 --> 00:07:51.480
Could it be?!

87
00:07:51.480 --> 00:07:53.160
Big Bro Luffy!

88
00:07:53.160 --> 00:07:54.280
What?!

89
00:07:54.280 --> 00:07:56.300
Hey, hang in there!

90
00:07:56.300 --> 00:07:58.240
Come to your senses!

91
00:08:09.800 --> 00:08:11.280
30 seconds!

92
00:08:11.280 --> 00:08:13.290
I won't last longer than that.

93
00:08:15.680 --> 00:08:16.970
Zoro!

94
00:08:17.490 --> 00:08:18.810
That'll be enough!

95
00:08:21.100 --> 00:08:23.900
There isn't a fountain over there.

96
00:08:23.900 --> 00:08:26.110
Could it be that rubber man?!

97
00:08:31.360 --> 00:08:32.600
Don't worry about that.

98
00:08:32.600 --> 00:08:35.280
It's nothing, you damn half-fish!

99
00:08:36.180 --> 00:08:40.830
I warned you not to 
say those words ever again,

100
00:08:40.830 --> 00:08:43.220
dead man!

101
00:08:48.440 --> 00:08:50.490
If I can smash that block with a kick,

102
00:08:50.490 --> 00:08:52.320
he can fight.

103
00:08:52.320 --> 00:08:56.470
Luffy, you're the only one who can settle this now!

104
00:09:00.430 --> 00:09:05.060
Those with devil fruit powers struggle to use those powers in the sea,

105
00:09:05.060 --> 00:09:08.780
let alone fight to survive, so he should be dead by now.

106
00:09:09.410 --> 00:09:12.300
If he's still alive,

107
00:09:12.300 --> 00:09:16.610
that means someone is interfering with our little game.

108
00:09:16.610 --> 00:09:17.990
Are you all right?!

109
00:09:17.990 --> 00:09:19.490
I'm glad you're okay!

110
00:09:19.490 --> 00:09:21.450
Yeah! Oh?

111
00:09:21.450 --> 00:09:22.620
What?! What's the matter?!

112
00:09:23.730 --> 00:09:25.600
Pops, what did you do 
with your pinwheel?

113
00:09:25.600 --> 00:09:26.620
It was so cool.

114
00:09:26.620 --> 00:09:29.460
Who cares about that right now?!

115
00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:32.550
Interfering?

116
00:09:32.550 --> 00:09:35.930
It didn't seem like a fair game
from the start.

117
00:09:36.560 --> 00:09:38.200
At any rate,

118
00:09:38.200 --> 00:09:40.890
if something's getting in the way, 
I need to check on it.

119
00:09:41.930 --> 00:09:43.510
Out of my way.

120
00:09:45.830 --> 00:09:47.200
Egg Star!

121
00:09:50.170 --> 00:09:52.320
I've got your back, Zoro!

122
00:09:52.840 --> 00:09:54.100
Big Bro Usopp!

123
00:09:54.100 --> 00:09:55.280
Is he all right?!

124
00:09:55.280 --> 00:09:58.660
How brave! What an epic arrival!

125
00:09:58.660 --> 00:10:00.850
Go for broke!

126
00:10:00.850 --> 00:10:03.120
That's where you are?!

127
00:10:03.820 --> 00:10:05.080
Usopp!

128
00:10:05.620 --> 00:10:06.790
Listen, Nami!

129
00:10:06.790 --> 00:10:08.440
I beat one of the officers!

130
00:10:08.440 --> 00:10:11.040
One of the officers! Me! I beat him!

131
00:10:11.040 --> 00:10:13.530
The guy with a face like this.

132
00:10:14.860 --> 00:10:17.050
Fishmen are a piece of cake!

133
00:10:20.010 --> 00:10:23.470
You defeated... Chew?!

134
00:10:24.770 --> 00:10:26.170
Serves you right!

135
00:10:26.170 --> 00:10:29.600
With my arrival, the fight suddenly reaches its climax!

136
00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:32.050
The final chapter begins!

137
00:10:35.230 --> 00:10:38.540
Hey, is there anything you can do to get out of this?

138
00:10:38.540 --> 00:10:39.890
Oh, that's impossible.

139
00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:41.950
I don't have any energy at all.

140
00:10:41.950 --> 00:10:45.770
Come out! Come out! Come out!

141
00:10:48.810 --> 00:10:50.670
Big Bro Cook!

142
00:10:50.670 --> 00:10:53.810
I don't know what's 
going on in the water,

143
00:10:53.810 --> 00:10:56.680
but he must be the key!

144
00:10:56.680 --> 00:10:58.090
Big Bro Zoro!

145
00:10:58.090 --> 00:11:00.930
Stand firm and stop Arlong!

146
00:11:02.850 --> 00:11:04.280
Okay!

147
00:11:04.280 --> 00:11:08.560
We have to somehow prevent Arlong 
from going into the sea, huh?

148
00:11:08.560 --> 00:11:10.560
I'll stop him from moving.

149
00:11:14.370 --> 00:11:18.150
I won't let you have your way!

150
00:11:18.150 --> 00:11:21.110
Hey, Arlong! Look here!

151
00:11:23.600 --> 00:11:25.810
Wha?! Big Bro Usopp!

152
00:11:25.810 --> 00:11:27.120
How brave!

153
00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:31.080
Usopp!

154
00:11:31.080 --> 00:11:33.850
Standing in my way
Rubber Band of Doom!

155
00:11:33.850 --> 00:11:37.800
leads me to believe you want to die first, Roronoa Zoro.

156
00:11:37.800 --> 00:11:40.160
Now! Go, Zoro!

157
00:11:40.160 --> 00:11:42.260
What are you trying to do?!

158
00:11:44.900 --> 00:11:46.500
No way will I die.

159
00:11:46.500 --> 00:11:49.820
I'll break that nose you're so proud of!

160
00:11:53.670 --> 00:11:55.020
You fool.

161
00:11:55.020 --> 00:11:58.480
I'm proud of it because it's unbreakable.

162
00:11:59.450 --> 00:12:02.700
If you were at your full strength,

163
00:12:02.700 --> 00:12:06.370
you might've been able to scratch it.

164
00:12:21.490 --> 00:12:22.780
Big Bro!

165
00:12:22.780 --> 00:12:24.360
Look over there!

166
00:12:24.360 --> 00:12:25.510
Hm?

167
00:12:26.010 --> 00:12:28.510
Ahh! That damn octopus is up!

168
00:12:30.460 --> 00:12:32.960
And... what the hell's he doing?

169
00:12:35.480 --> 00:12:38.970
Dammit! I thought the rubber band
was going to hit me!

170
00:12:38.970 --> 00:12:43.030
What?!

171
00:12:44.390 --> 00:12:47.550
See?! He was my target!

172
00:12:47.550 --> 00:12:49.740
You yelled, "Arlong," didn't you?

173
00:12:51.270 --> 00:12:52.460
The octopus.

174
00:12:52.960 --> 00:12:57.510
Roronoa Zoro! I won't 
let you have your way!

175
00:12:57.510 --> 00:13:01.390
I'll crush your friend 
who went into the sea!

176
00:13:08.330 --> 00:13:13.350
You don't have to be concerned 
since you'll all be dead, after all.

177
00:13:19.980 --> 00:13:23.010
Big Bro!

178
00:13:54.670 --> 00:13:56.280
Nami's big sister!

179
00:13:56.280 --> 00:13:57.980
Leave the rest to me!

180
00:14:01.940 --> 00:14:03.250
A fishman!

181
00:14:05.190 --> 00:14:06.730
Move away, Big Sister.

182
00:14:06.730 --> 00:14:08.700
I'll break that rock with my kick!

183
00:14:14.600 --> 00:14:15.580
That octopus!

184
00:14:15.580 --> 00:14:19.380
Takoyaki Punch!

185
00:14:19.380 --> 00:14:20.920
Big Sister!

186
00:14:26.040 --> 00:14:27.970
Zoro!

187
00:14:31.820 --> 00:14:33.960
So that was it?

188
00:14:33.960 --> 00:14:35.930
That was too quick.

189
00:14:36.560 --> 00:14:40.430
What's up with these bandages?

190
00:14:41.850 --> 00:14:44.190
Did you fall down or something?

191
00:14:48.280 --> 00:14:50.260
What's this scar?

192
00:15:04.520 --> 00:15:07.940
How can he still be alive 
with wounds like this?

193
00:15:08.510 --> 00:15:11.470
How can he still be standing?!

194
00:15:22.810 --> 00:15:25.370
What is that look in his eyes?

195
00:15:25.370 --> 00:15:28.110
Is that the look of someone who's dying?

196
00:15:30.070 --> 00:15:32.360
He's a man I need to kill for sure,

197
00:15:32.360 --> 00:15:37.290
right here, right now!

198
00:15:44.500 --> 00:15:46.800
Staying still...

199
00:15:46.800 --> 00:15:49.660
would have kept some of the wounds from opening.

200
00:15:49.660 --> 00:15:52.400
That's right.

201
00:15:52.400 --> 00:15:54.750
You find your situation amusing?

202
00:15:58.350 --> 00:16:01.110
I'm not talking about me.

203
00:16:01.110 --> 00:16:03.120
I'm talking about the octofreak.

204
00:16:03.810 --> 00:16:05.180
What?!

205
00:16:05.180 --> 00:16:06.990
I thought I told you,

206
00:16:06.990 --> 00:16:09.870
we win this game.

207
00:16:19.660 --> 00:16:22.410
Dammit!

208
00:16:22.410 --> 00:16:25.170
That scared the crap outta me!

209
00:16:28.550 --> 00:16:32.300
You're the one who complicated everything in the first place!

210
00:16:34.760 --> 00:16:36.220
He did it!

211
00:16:36.220 --> 00:16:38.720
Go beat down that shark bastard,

212
00:16:38.720 --> 00:16:41.680
you damn idiot!

213
00:16:43.460 --> 00:16:45.200
Is it coming, kid?

214
00:16:45.200 --> 00:16:47.270
It's coming!

215
00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:59.910
Wahhhhh! I'm back!

216
00:17:02.370 --> 00:17:03.830
Rubber boy!

217
00:17:03.830 --> 00:17:06.830
Big Bro Luffy!

218
00:17:13.410 --> 00:17:14.510
Luffy!

219
00:17:17.980 --> 00:17:20.140
That damn rubber jerk!

220
00:17:21.240 --> 00:17:23.140
You're late, idiot!

221
00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:25.980
Zoro!

222
00:17:26.570 --> 00:17:27.350
Huh?

223
00:17:27.900 --> 00:17:29.690
Hey! Stop it!

224
00:17:29.690 --> 00:17:30.820
You wouldn't!

225
00:17:35.430 --> 00:17:37.470
It's my turn!

226
00:17:39.370 --> 00:17:41.200
You idiot!

227
00:17:41.200 --> 00:17:43.660
Gum-Gum...

228
00:17:43.660 --> 00:17:46.370
Bell...

229
00:17:46.930 --> 00:17:47.830
and...

230
00:17:47.830 --> 00:17:50.000
Whip!

231
00:17:56.630 --> 00:17:58.590
Gum-Gum...

232
00:17:58.590 --> 00:17:59.800
Pistol!

233
00:18:04.430 --> 00:18:06.810
Gatling!

234
00:18:15.920 --> 00:18:17.300
All right!

235
00:18:34.090 --> 00:18:36.550
Did you do something?

236
00:18:36.550 --> 00:18:39.130
He didn't feel a thing!

237
00:18:39.760 --> 00:18:42.300
Yep. That was my warm-up.

238
00:18:44.160 --> 00:18:45.930
That idiot!

239
00:18:45.930 --> 00:18:47.570
I'm gonna kill him!

240
00:18:51.270 --> 00:18:55.110
It's admirable how you scum have held on by the skin of your teeth.

241
00:18:56.100 --> 00:19:00.700
Though, you'd have been happier dying at the bottom of the sea.

242
00:19:00.700 --> 00:19:02.170
Hm? Not really.

243
00:19:02.170 --> 00:19:04.950
I'm glad they saved me.

244
00:19:05.800 --> 00:19:08.660
Can you understand my anger?

245
00:19:08.660 --> 00:19:13.250
It's the anger of seeing my dear 
brothers crushed by worms.

246
00:19:13.250 --> 00:19:19.340
You'll soon wish that you 
had submitted to your deaths.

247
00:19:19.810 --> 00:19:22.410
Is Big Bro Luffy gonna be okay?

248
00:19:22.410 --> 00:19:26.010
His furious assault had no effect whatsoever.

249
00:19:26.010 --> 00:19:29.810
More importantly, how far did Big Bro Zoro fly?!

250
00:19:29.810 --> 00:19:33.390
Go Luffy! I've got your back!

251
00:19:33.390 --> 00:19:35.020
You don't have to worry 
about his back.

252
00:19:41.510 --> 00:19:45.620
If he loses, you guys will all die, too.

253
00:19:46.090 --> 00:19:47.530
Yeah, we will.

254
00:19:47.530 --> 00:19:50.390
If that happens, it's the end for the East Blue, as well.

255
00:19:52.390 --> 00:19:55.960
What's the bleak difference between you and me?

256
00:19:57.230 --> 00:19:58.400
Our noses.

257
00:20:01.380 --> 00:20:02.380
Our jaws?

258
00:20:04.510 --> 00:20:07.250
I wonder if Big Bro's joking.

259
00:20:07.250 --> 00:20:10.350
No, he's definitely serious.

260
00:20:10.350 --> 00:20:11.810
Our webs!

261
00:20:13.150 --> 00:20:15.190
It's our race!

262
00:20:28.160 --> 00:20:30.620
Such a fool! He hurt himself 
by biting on a rock!

263
00:20:30.620 --> 00:20:32.830
Now his teeth are crack–

264
00:20:36.380 --> 00:20:39.800
He crushed the stone 
pillar with his teeth!

265
00:20:39.800 --> 00:20:42.440
Ahh! That's scary!

266
00:21:02.220 --> 00:21:03.380
Did you see...

267
00:21:04.660 --> 00:21:07.270
the inherent power of a fishman?

268
00:21:07.270 --> 00:21:12.700
Heaven created you humans to have you bow before fishmen.

269
00:21:13.600 --> 00:21:16.100
You're inferior creatures.

270
00:21:16.100 --> 00:21:20.080
We're on a different level 
from the moment we're born.

271
00:21:29.410 --> 00:21:33.100
I'll show you the real difference between you and me.

272
00:21:33.100 --> 00:21:35.090
Oh, yeah? Let's see it.

273
00:21:35.090 --> 00:21:37.190
There's no way I'm losing to you.

274
00:21:37.190 --> 00:21:40.240
I am the man who'll be 
king of the pirates!

275
00:21:58.610 --> 00:22:00.290
King of the pirates?

276
00:22:00.730 --> 00:22:02.320
Don't make me laugh.

277
00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:06.300
Can you inferior humans do something like...

278
00:22:07.190 --> 00:22:09.730
crush a pillar with your teeth?

279
00:22:10.760 --> 00:22:12.620
If that jaw gets you,

280
00:22:12.620 --> 00:22:14.850
it won't just leave bite marks...

281
00:22:20.240 --> 00:22:22.650
it'll tear clear through your bones!

282
00:22:25.690 --> 00:22:27.520
So what?!

283
00:22:28.030 --> 00:22:29.350
Stop...

284
00:22:31.400 --> 00:22:33.790
bragging over stuff like that!

285
00:22:36.520 --> 00:22:39.780
I can break stone without biting it.

286
00:22:44.400 --> 00:22:46.730
Nice! Score one for Big Bro Luffy!

287
00:22:46.730 --> 00:22:49.420
That's right! 
The result's the same!

288
00:22:50.640 --> 00:22:53.560
Th-That's beside the point!

289
00:22:54.060 --> 00:22:57.040
Humans are stupid and weak.

290
00:22:57.040 --> 00:23:00.370
If you fall into water and can't pull yourself out,

291
00:23:00.370 --> 00:23:01.690
then what'll you do?!

292
00:23:05.150 --> 00:23:09.410
Nothing! That's why I need help!

293
00:23:14.680 --> 00:23:17.120
Hm? He can also use swords?

294
00:23:20.750 --> 00:23:22.080
Take that... and that... and that!

295
00:23:22.080 --> 00:23:23.590
What're you doing?

296
00:23:23.590 --> 00:23:28.720
It looks like you're just 
swinging those blades around.

297
00:23:36.410 --> 00:23:39.140
I'm not looking to play your little game.

298
00:23:48.700 --> 00:23:50.530
I've had enough of this nonsense.

299
00:23:50.530 --> 00:23:52.520
Clench your teeth!

300
00:24:14.150 --> 00:24:17.390
Wha...?! He shattered Arlong's teeth!

301
00:24:21.700 --> 00:24:25.980
I don't know how to use swords, you bastard!

302
00:24:28.980 --> 00:24:32.200
Huh? What's he saying that now for?

303
00:24:32.720 --> 00:24:35.110
I don't know how to sail.

304
00:24:36.710 --> 00:24:38.640
I can't cook.

305
00:24:40.610 --> 00:24:42.310
I can't lie, either.

306
00:24:42.310 --> 00:24:43.430
Hey!

307
00:24:43.960 --> 00:24:48.050
I'm confident that I can't 
live without help!

308
00:24:52.160 --> 00:24:55.840
Fully admitting how 
pathetic you are...

309
00:24:55.840 --> 00:24:58.000
You sure are honest.

310
00:24:58.620 --> 00:25:03.130
I bet your crew is 
bothered by having

311
00:25:03.130 --> 00:25:06.020
such an incompetent captain like you.

312
00:25:06.680 --> 00:25:12.490
I wonder why your crew tried 
so desperately to save you.

313
00:25:12.960 --> 00:25:18.570
How can someone like you, with no damn pride, be a pirate captain?

314
00:25:18.570 --> 00:25:20.660
What in the world can you do?

315
00:25:23.000 --> 00:25:25.250
I can defeat you!
